sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K862002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part was constructed by standard cloning from parts BBa_K862003 (precB) and BBa_K173004 (LacZ).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a part for the precise quantification of UV-radiation or radioactive radiation in E. coli (recA+) strains, i.e. BL21(DE3). It consits of a recB Promoter (part BBa_K862003) fused to a LacZ reporter cloned in front of a double terminator (part BBa_K173004).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part was first constructed in plasmid backbone pSB1AK3 and then subcloned into pSB1C3 for submission to the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Charlotte Bunne, Mariam Harmouche, Stefan Holderbach, Anna Huhn and Jakob Kreft (in alphabetical order)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K173004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lorenzo Pasotti, Susanna Schiavi, Letizia Diamante, Paolo Magni

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: precB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: E. coli MG1655 genome: http://ecoliwiki.net/colipedia/index.php/recB:Gene bp -70 to -1 before recB coding sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The recB promoter sequence was taken for the E. coli MG1655 genome sequence (http://ecoliwiki.net/colipedia/index.php/recB:Gene). We assumed the main promoter region to be located from -70 to -1 bp upstream the recB start codon. Therefore this sequence was synthesized and cloned on an oligo basis.
We will not submit the physical DNA of this part, but we provide the oligo-sequences you can use for synthesizing and cloning this part in front of any EcoRI/XbaI precut reporter part.
RecB_fw: aattcgcggccgcttctagagCCTGAAGGCTGGAAAGTGTGGGAGAACGTCAGCGCGTTGCAGCAAACAATGCCCCTGATGAGTGAAAAGAc RecB_rev: ctaggTCTTTTCACTCATCAGGGGCATTGTTTGCTGCAACGCGCTGACGTTCTCCCACACTTTCCAGCCTTCAGGctctagaagcggccgcg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: the sequence was ordered on a synthetic oligo basis and cloned in front of EcoRI/XbaI reporter parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Charlotte Bunne, Mariam Harmouche, Stefan Holderbach, Anna Huhn and Jakob Kreft (in alphabetical order)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR amplified and standardized from BL21
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LacZ encodes beta-galactosidase, an intracellular enzyme that cleaves the disaccharide lactose into glucose and galactose. Beta-galactosidase can also cleaves X-gal and ONPG into colorful products.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhan Jian
